postcontent:
What happens after you pull the trigger in a self defense situation?  I feel so strongly about helping people protect themselves and the service I am about to share with you that  I WILL GLADLY PAY FOR YOUR FIRST MONTH OF SERVICE!

With my background in law enforcement and as an instructor for Concealed Firearms Permits, Firearms Training and Self Defense training, my students ask me a lot of questions about armed self defense.  One of the most common questions is about what to do AFTER a self defense shooting.

For a long time, that was a hard question to answer, because it involves what to say or not to say, finding a good lawyer, saving up a few thousand dollars for legal fees, and so on. There are a hundred ways to do the wrong thing and end up in trouble even if you legally defend yourself and/or a loved one.  Not to mention the emotional and psychological effects that you may deal with after defending yourself and/or a loved one.

Recently, I’ve just been telling people to join Second Call Defense.  My wife and I are members and I strongly urge you to join as well. Remember, I’ll PAY FOR YOUR FIRST MONTH!

Second Call Defense is an organization that provides complete legal protection for armed self defense. If you have to defend yourself with a gun, all you have to do is call 911 to report the incident then immediately call the Second Call Defense hotline.  Starting at only $8.95 a month.

An actual attorney will answer the phone 24 hours a day / 7 days a week, to help you deal with the immediate aftermath, including how to properly deal with law-enforcement. They will also research attorneys in your area and refer you to several of the best within 24 hours, immediately wire a retainer to the attorney of your choice and make arrangements for bail if things get that far.

And if things get really bad and you end up prosecuted or sued, your membership also includes criminal defense reimbursement, accidental shooting protection, and depending on your level of membership, civil suit defense protection and civil suit damages protection, all of which is backed by the National Rifle Association (NRA) endorsed insurance program.  In addition to all that, they also provide psychological support, dependent upon your level of membership.

This protection covers you everywhere within the United States.  Have peace of mind no matter where you are, be it in your home, on vacation or even traveling. 

I have several friends and acquaintances, both civilians and law enforcement, who I know personally, that have been placed in a situation where they have had to use lethal force to defend themselves or others.  Many of them have had to deal with law suits and other legal ramifications, and several have spent tens of thousands of dollars in legal fees, on a fully justified self defense situation, in which no criminal charges were ever filed.  Not to mention the emotional and psychological aftermath of an armed self defense encounter.

like I said, I strongly urge you to join. And yes, I will pay for your first month.

HERE’S WHAT I SUGGEST:

1. Click here to go to the Second Call Defense website at:  
http://www.secondcalldefense.org/plans-and-pricing?affiliate=20469

2. Select the membership level you want. Then click the JOIN button for that level.   YOU WILL AUTOMATICALLY GET YOUR FIRST MONTH FREE.

The way this works is: you will see a charge for your first month on your credit card bill, but you’ll get a check for the full amount of your first month in your Membership Kit mailed to you about a week after you sign up. That makes your First Month Free.

You can change your membership level or cancel at any time. But please, at least try it for a month. It’s the easiest and most practical way to answer the question “What do I do AFTER a self defense shooting?”

Whether you carry a concealed weapon on a regular basis, only once in a while or just keep one in the home for defense, this service will give you the peace of mind you need.  Don’t chance losing your hard earned savings, your home or your quality of life.  Join today, it’s an investment that could protect your future and save you a lot of heartache later.

If you have any questions, email me or give me a call.
